@StoicChampion  
It took some time to figure out how to dismantle your combination, but [Phantasmal Image](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Phantasmal Image) can do it. If I can't cast blue spells, then I will use black to get it into my graveyard and reanimate it. You can save yourself with ghostway, but I can deplete you of those by casting/reanimating a clone each turn.  
You need a [painter's servant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=painter's servant) too...and while you're at it, why not add a [douse](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=douse)?  
I think [Magus of the Tabernacle](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Magus of the Tabernacle) gets around this too.  

@igniteice   
Note that not all of those work, because there is a rule of law in play, but a couple of those are super.
